Financial Instruments 

We estimate the fair value of financial instruments where appropriate. The assumptions we use &#8212; including the discount rate and estimates of cash flows &#8212; can significantly affect the fair value. These values are estimates and may not match the amounts we would realize upon sale or settlement of our financial positions. 

